    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mechanical lamps which have a spring-driven pump to maintain a uniform flow of oil to the top of the wick. Developed in France by Carcel in 1798.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
